article.headline: Delaware St. 67, Bethune-Cookman 50
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- Marcus Neal scored 17 points, including a pair of 3-pointers late in the first half, to lead Delaware State to a 67-50 victory over Bethune-Cookman on Saturday. Neal's 3-pointer with 2:00 left in the half gave the Hornets (13-9, 8-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) a 32-27 lead, and he hit another with 37 seconds left for a 35-27 halftime lead. Jay Threatt assisted on both shots and finished the game with 10 assists. The Hornets' lead reached double figures when Frisco Sandidge's layup made it 49-39 with 11:45 remaining. Sandidge scored eight of his 14 points in the second half. Kevin Dukes scored 12 points on four 3-pointers to lead the Wildcats (14-11, 6-5). He made two in the opening 2:38 to give Bethune-Cookman an 8-4 lead, and his other two came in the opening 1:01 of the second half to cut Delaware State's lead to 35-33.
